📦 2. OrderedDict

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is OrderedDict?

```text id="ordereddict_def"
OrderedDict remembers the order in which items were inserted.
```

---

💻 Example

```python id="ordereddict_example"
from collections import OrderedDict

data = OrderedDict()

data["A"] = 1
data["B"] = 2
data["C"] = 3

print(data)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="ordereddict_output"
OrderedDict([('A', 1), ('B', 2), ('C', 3)])
```

---

📌 Note

From Python 3.7+, normal dictionaries also preserve insertion order.

However, `OrderedDict` provides extra ordering methods.

---

💻 Move Element to End

```python id="ordereddict_move"
from collections import OrderedDict

data = OrderedDict([
    ("A", 1),
    ("B", 2),
    ("C", 3)
])

data.move_to_end("A")

print(data)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="ordereddict_move_output"
OrderedDict([('B', 2), ('C', 3), ('A', 1)])
```

