🗂️ 3. defaultdict

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is defaultdict?

```text id="defaultdict_def"
defaultdict automatically creates a default value for missing keys.
```

---

❌ Normal Dictionary Example

```python id="normal_dict_error"
data = {}

print(data["name"])
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="key_error_output"
KeyError
```

---

✅ defaultdict Example

```python id="defaultdict_example"
from collections import defaultdict

data = defaultdict(str)

print(data["name"])
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="defaultdict_output"
```

(Empty String)

---

💻 Integer Default Value

```python id="defaultdict_int"
from collections import defaultdict

count = defaultdict(int)

count["apple"] += 1

print(count)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="defaultdict_int_output"
defaultdict(<class 'int'>, {'apple': 1})
```

---

💻 Grouping Example

```python id="grouping_example"
from collections import defaultdict

students = [
    ("Python", "Alex"),
    ("Java", "John"),
    ("Python", "Emma")
]

groups = defaultdict(list)

for course, student in students:
    groups[course].append(student)

print(groups)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="grouping_output"
{
 'Python': ['Alex', 'Emma'],
 'Java': ['John']
}
```

