🔄 4. deque

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is deque?

```text id="deque_def"
deque (double-ended queue) allows fast insertion and deletion from both ends.
```

---

💻 Example

```python id="deque_example"
from collections import deque

dq = deque([1, 2, 3])

print(dq)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="deque_output"
deque([1, 2, 3])
```

---

➕ Add Elements

```python id="deque_append"
from collections import deque

dq = deque([1, 2])

dq.append(3)
dq.appendleft(0)

print(dq)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="deque_append_output"
deque([0, 1, 2, 3])
```

---

❌ Remove Elements

```python id="deque_pop"
from collections import deque

dq = deque([1, 2, 3])

dq.pop()
dq.popleft()

print(dq)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="deque_pop_output"
deque([2])
```

---

🎯 Why deque is Faster

For large datasets:

✔ Fast insertion at beginning
✔ Fast deletion at beginning
✔ Better than lists for queue operations

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📊 Comparison

| Feature      | List | deque |
| ------------ | ---- | ----- |
| Append Right | Fast | Fast  |
| Pop Right    | Fast | Fast  |
| Append Left  | Slow | Fast  |
| Pop Left     | Slow | Fast  |

